window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>\"An inspiring read for anyone wanting to downsize, finally park the car in the garage, or just clear out a few closets.\"</b> (Rachel Jonat, <i>TheMinimalistMom.com</i>)</p> <p>Having less stuff is the key to happiness: Do you ever feel overwhelmed, instead of overjoyed, by all your possessions? Do you secretly wish a gale force wind would blow the clutter from your home? If so, it's time to simplify your life! <i>The Joy of Less</i> is a fun, lighthearted guide to minimalist living:</p> <ul> <li>Part one provides an inspirational pep talk on the joys and rewards of paring down.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li> <li>Part two presents the Streamline method: 10 easy steps to rid your house of clutter.</li> <li>Part three goes room by room, outlining specific ways to tackle each one.</li> <li>Part four helps you get your family on board and live more lightly and gracefully on the Earth.</li> </ul> <p>Ready to sweep away the clutter? Just listen to this book, and you'll be on your way to a simpler, more streamlined, and more serene life.&nbsp;</p> <p>Francine has helped hundreds of thousands of people declutter their homes and simplify their lives with her best-selling book, <i>The Joy of Less</i>.</p> <p>Her advice has been featured widely in the media, including on CNN, BBC, <i>Today</i>, and in <i>The New York Times</i>, <i>USA Today</i>, <i>The Chicago Tribune</i>, <i>The Guardian</i>,<i> The Financial Times</i>, <i>Forbes</i>, <i>The Huffington Post</i>,<i> Le Parisien</i>, <i>ELLE Espana</i>, <i>House Beautiful</i>, <i>Woman's World</i>, <i>Dr. Oz</i>, <i>The Good Life</i>, and others.</p> <p><i>The Joy of Less</i>, a beautiful minimalism book, makes an ideal gift for any loved one on a mission to simplify their life.</p>"; 
